- "opening match of each tournament" refers to the first match in the sequence of matches for each tournament;
- "top 3 run scorers" means the players who scored the most runs in their respective matches.

- 'Top batsman' refers to the batsman with the highest career average in their country;
- 'Top bowler' refers to the bowler with the lowest career average in their country;
- 'Performance in matches' includes various statistics such as runs, wickets, and strike rate.

